perl-File-Find-Rule
-------------------------------------------
File::Find::Rule is a friendlier interface to File::Find. It allows you 
to build rules which specify the desired files and directories.

Runtime requirements:
  perl-5.10.0-5
  perl-Number-Compare-0.01-3
  perl-Text-Glob-0.08-2

Canonical homepage:
  http://search.cpan.org/~rclamp/File-Find-Rule/

Canonical download:
  http://www.cpan.org/authors/id/R/RC/RCLAMP/

-------------------------------------------

Build instructions:
  unpack perl-File-Find-Rule-0.30-X-src.tar.bz2
    if you use setup to install this src package, it will be
	 unpacked under /usr/src automatically
  cd /usr/src
  cygport ./perl-File-Find-Rule-0.30-X.cygport all

This will create:
  /usr/src/perl-File-Find-Rule-0.30-X-src.tar.bz2
  /usr/src/perl-File-Find-Rule-0.30-X.tar.bz2

-------------------------------------------

Port Notes:

----- version 0.30-2 -----
Initial release for Cygwin 1.7.


Cygwin port maintained by:
